  "description": "Tests ability to find ovarian cancer patients via standard chemotherapy regimens. First-line is platinum-taxane (carboplatin + paclitaxel). Cisplatin is older platinum agent. Gemcitabine is used in recurrence. Olaparib is the first PARP inhibitor for BRCA-mutated ovarian cancer.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed ovarian cancer chemotherapy including carboplatin, paclitaxel, cisplatin, gemcitabine, or olaparib.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on ovarian chemo.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed ovarian cancer chemotherapy \u2014 platinum agents (carboplatin, cisplatin), taxanes (paclitaxel), nucleoside analogs (gemcitabine), and PARP inhibitors (olaparib, used for BRCA-mutated maintenance therapy).",
    "expert": "I need MedicationRequest resources for any ovarian cancer chemotherapy. Use these RxNorm ingredient codes: 40048 (carboplatin), 56946 (paclitaxel), 2555 (cisplatin), 12574 (gemcitabine), 1597582 (olaparib). Combine in a single comma-separated code search. Note carboplatin/paclitaxel is the first-line regimen; cisplatin/gemcitabine cross-indicated with other cancers; olaparib is highly ovarian-specific."
